### decodeWaitcnt() {#a0d3e0a75774a86f6c8302eee2dfe1326}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>void llvm::AMDGPU::decodeWaitcnt (<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/amdgpu/isaversion">IsaVersion</a> &amp; Version, unsigned Waitcnt, unsigned &amp; Vmcnt, unsigned &amp; Expcnt, unsigned &amp; Lgkmcnt)</>}>
Decodes Vmcnt, Expcnt and Lgkmcnt from given <code><a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/amdgpu/waitcnt">Waitcnt</a></code> for given isa <code>Version</code>, and writes decoded values into <code>Vmcnt</code>, <code>Expcnt</code> and <code>Lgkmcnt</code> respectively.

Should not be used on gfx12+, the instruction which needs it is deprecated

<code>Vmcnt</code>, <code>Expcnt</code> and <code>Lgkmcnt</code> are decoded as follows: <code>Vmcnt</code> = <code><a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/amdgpu/waitcnt">Waitcnt</a></code>&#91;3:0&#93; (pre-gfx9) <code>Vmcnt</code> = <code><a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/amdgpu/waitcnt">Waitcnt</a></code>&#91;15:14,3:0&#93; (gfx9,10) <code>Vmcnt</code> = <code><a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/amdgpu/waitcnt">Waitcnt</a></code>&#91;15:10&#93; (gfx11) <code>Expcnt</code> = <code><a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/amdgpu/waitcnt">Waitcnt</a></code>&#91;6:4&#93; (pre-gfx11) <code>Expcnt</code> = <code><a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/amdgpu/waitcnt">Waitcnt</a></code>&#91;2:0&#93; (gfx11) <code>Lgkmcnt</code> = <code><a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/amdgpu/waitcnt">Waitcnt</a></code>&#91;11:8&#93; (pre-gfx10) <code>Lgkmcnt</code> = <code><a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/amdgpu/waitcnt">Waitcnt</a></code>&#91;13:8&#93; (gfx10) <code>Lgkmcnt</code> = <code><a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/amdgpu/waitcnt">Waitcnt</a></code>&#91;9:4&#93; (gfx11)

Encodes <code>Vmcnt</code>, <code>Expcnt</code> and <code>Lgkmcnt</code> into <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/amdgpu/waitcnt">Waitcnt</a> for given isa <code>Version</code>.

Should not be used on gfx12+, the instruction which needs it is deprecated

<code>Vmcnt</code>, <code>Expcnt</code> and <code>Lgkmcnt</code> are encoded as follows: <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/amdgpu/waitcnt">Waitcnt</a>&#91;2:0&#93; = <code>Expcnt</code> (gfx11+) <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/amdgpu/waitcnt">Waitcnt</a>&#91;3:0&#93; = <code>Vmcnt</code> (pre-gfx9) <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/amdgpu/waitcnt">Waitcnt</a>&#91;3:0&#93; = <code>Vmcnt</code>&#91;3:0&#93; (gfx9,10) <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/amdgpu/waitcnt">Waitcnt</a>&#91;6:4&#93; = <code>Expcnt</code> (pre-gfx11) <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/amdgpu/waitcnt">Waitcnt</a>&#91;9:4&#93; = <code>Lgkmcnt</code> (gfx11) <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/amdgpu/waitcnt">Waitcnt</a>&#91;11:8&#93; = <code>Lgkmcnt</code> (pre-gfx10) <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/amdgpu/waitcnt">Waitcnt</a>&#91;13:8&#93; = <code>Lgkmcnt</code> (gfx10) <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/amdgpu/waitcnt">Waitcnt</a>&#91;15:10&#93; = <code>Vmcnt</code> (gfx11) <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/amdgpu/waitcnt">Waitcnt</a>&#91;15:14&#93; = <code>Vmcnt</code>&#91;5:4&#93; (gfx9,10)


<SectionUser title="Returns">
<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/amdgpu/waitcnt">Waitcnt</a> with encoded <code>Vmcnt</code>, <code>Expcnt</code> and <code>Lgkmcnt</code> for given isa <code>Version</code>.
</SectionUser>

  prototype={<>std::pair&lt; unsigned, unsigned &gt; llvm::AMDGPU::getShiftMask (unsigned Value)</>}
  labels = {["constexpr"]}>
Deduce the least significant bit aligned shift and mask values for a binary Complement <code><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/value">Value</a></code> (as they&#39;re defined in <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/amdgpu/sidefines-h">SIDefines.h</a> as C&#95;&#42;) as a returned pair&lt;shift, mask&gt;.

### maskShiftGet() {#a8749a42239506716ab09647dd0b31795}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>const MCExpr &#42; llvm::AMDGPU::maskShiftGet (<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcexpr">MCExpr</a> &#42; Val, uint32&#95;t Mask, uint32&#95;t Shift, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mccontext">MCContext</a> &amp; Ctx)</>}
  labels = {["inline"]}>
Provided with the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcexpr">MCExpr</a> &#42; <code>Val</code>, uint32 <code>Mask</code> and <code>Shift</code>, will return the right shifted and masked, in said order of operations, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcexpr">MCExpr</a> &#42; created within the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mccontext">MCContext</a> <code>Ctx</code>.

For example, given <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcexpr">MCExpr</a> &#42;Val, Mask == 0xf, Shift == 6 the returned <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcexpr">MCExpr</a>
<ul>

### maskShiftSet() {#a5f3ff39c7ddc47c851a92a89a6c68e3d}

For example, given <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcexpr">MCExpr</a> &#42;Val, Mask == 0xf, Shift == 6 the returned <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcexpr">MCExpr</a>
<ul>
